Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you applied\Nto the School for Kingdom Evangelizers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.05,0:00:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but not been invited?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Or have you wanted to apply
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.72,0:00:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but wondered if the time was right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.22,0:00:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the pandemic,\Nclasses are still suspended.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.98,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you are a pioneer\Nbetween the ages of 23 and 65
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.23,0:00:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and would like to attend\Na future class of SKE,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.24,0:00:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,please contact your congregation secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.03,0:00:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and fill out the online application
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it can be considered\Nwhen classes resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.25,0:01:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As a reminder, your application\Nis active for one year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.08,0:01:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you must apply each year\Nthat you desire to be considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.22,0:01:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, we are pleased to inform you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.68,0:01:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that graduates\Nof the Ministerial Training School
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.39,0:01:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or the Bible School for Single Brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.97,0:01:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who are still single and in full-time service
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.48,0:01:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,may now apply\Nfor the School for Kingdom Evangelizers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.86,0:01:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to maintain our peace
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.28,0:01:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,when dealing with intense trials\Nand pressures?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.16,0:01:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Jehovah care for our needs\Nwhen we are in distress?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.58,0:01:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The following video will introduce us\Nto brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.00,0:01:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been blessed by Jehovah\Nwith peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The title is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.71,0:01:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}How Our Brothers Are Enjoying Peace
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.30,0:01:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Despite . . . Opposition, Illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:01:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Economic Problems, Natural Disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we live in Satan’s world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.57,0:02:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us will face situations
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.41,0:02:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that can rob us of our peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Regaining that peace can be difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.41,0:02:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In this video, we will hear
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.71,0:02:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from three sisters and two couples
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.00,0:02:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,who will speak candidly about their trials
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.26,0:02:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they struggled to cope with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.88,0:02:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But in spite of what they have endured,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.68,0:02:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,please take note of their smiles, their joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.10,0:02:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they did to regain\Nand maintain their peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.94,0:02:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And take special note\Nof how Jehovah helped them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.28,0:02:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body knows that many of you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.87,0:03:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are suffering circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.12,0:03:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,not unlike the ones we will hear about,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.33,0:03:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and they trust that the examples\Nin this video
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.29,0:03:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,will help each of you to maintain your peace
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.09,0:03:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as you endure various trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.06,0:03:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters all over the world\Nare facing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.23,0:03:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,natural disasters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,economic collapse,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.61,0:03:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.74,0:03:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and persecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.53,0:03:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.03,0:03:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they keep joy and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.83,0:03:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can learn a lot from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Antoinette.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.00,0:03:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I live here in Las Vegas, Nevada,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.05,0:03:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with my supermom
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.55,0:03:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and my troublemaking sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.43,0:04:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Family and friends have always been\Nimportant to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.43,0:04:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As a child, I lived with my mom and dad
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was very close\Nto my dad’s side of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.85,0:04:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very loving, unified, and fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was pretty happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But I already was starting to feel\Nthe effects of my cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.62,0:04:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We just didn’t know what it was really.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.87,0:04:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One day I was OK, and then the next day\NI started feeling bad, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In my childhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.17,0:04:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I played an unusual game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.97,0:04:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I would catch insects,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,put them in a jar, and then bring them home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.31,0:04:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I would get books,\Nsuch as the Criminal Procedural Code,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.65,0:04:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,open them up,\Nand start judging one of the bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.44,0:05:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I would play the role\Nof investigator and judge at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.41,0:05:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born into a family where everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with my grandparents,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.71,0:05:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,was either wearing an officer’s uniform\Nor a judge’s robe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.46,0:05:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why I had\Nthis strong sense of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.26,0:05:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But in 1989,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.93,0:05:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother was in a tragic car accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.77,0:05:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.43,0:05:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,she got severe burns
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.02,0:05:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,on her face, hands, and body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.36,0:05:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then my father,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.69,0:05:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at seeing my mom’s condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.40,0:05:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.78,0:05:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was at that moment, I guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.50,0:05:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that my world, my ideals,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:05:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,they crumbled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As a little kid, I always wanted, like,\None big happy family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.47,0:06:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we moved to New York for my treatment,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I no longer had that big family bond anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What I was feeling back then in New York was
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,just sadness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.61,0:06:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,never really peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.49,0:06:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in California,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.87,0:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re used to fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.17,0:06:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I got the call to evacuate\Nthat morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.84,0:06:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I never knew that by that evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.59,0:06:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole town of Paradise would be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.61,0:07:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before the fire,\Nwe had the needs of the congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.82,0:07:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,where they instructed us\Nwhat to do in the case of a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.53,0:07:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the truck full of gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.49,0:07:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I had my go bag ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.37,0:07:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had a map of where I was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.21,0:07:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.63,0:07:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers, also in their instructions,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.34,0:07:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,said to obey the traffic instructors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The instructor told us to turn right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn’t want to turn right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.01,0:07:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but they said obey them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.60,0:07:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I turned right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,though I thought it would be really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The smoke got darker and darker,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally it got black.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.00,0:07:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn’t see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.67,0:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom has always told me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.76,0:08:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’ve always been
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.63,0:08:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a caregiver ever since I was a little girl;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.93,0:08:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it was just part of who I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.60,0:08:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t like to see people suffer;\Nit’s very difficult for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that when I first started working\Nas a nurse,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.82,0:08:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I would always cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.45,0:08:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I cried—\NLiterally I cried
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.62,0:08:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,every day that I had to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.21,0:08:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only was I overwhelmed\Nbeing a new nurse
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.79,0:08:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but also
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was battling my depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.01,0:08:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:08:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the treasurer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.35,0:08:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for a prestigious bank in Nicaragua,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.93,0:08:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was the father of a one-year-old son.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.18,0:09:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.90,0:09:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I lost my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.61,0:09:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, ‘I have the experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.36,0:09:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah will help me find another job,\Nsomething similar.’
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.99,0:09:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I kept looking for jobs,\Nbut doors kept closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.62,0:09:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt very tense;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.04,0:09:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it made me feel very useless,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.71,0:09:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.21,0:09:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t even provide for my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.09,0:09:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was something very difficult for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.06,0:09:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,These dear brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.02,0:09:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,faced serious challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.81,0:09:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They may have had moments\Nwhen they felt like Job
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,when he said: “I loathe my life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.15,0:09:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not an unusual human emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.99,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes things in life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.33,0:10:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t work out as we had hoped,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.29,0:10:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it can hurt us deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.63,0:10:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean that we are helpless victims\Nof our circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pay close attention
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.39,0:10:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and take note of why we can say
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.93,0:10:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that Margaret, Feliks,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.18,0:10:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Miguel, Nikki, and Antoinette
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.77,0:10:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are not helpless victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.52,0:10:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To the contrary,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.52,0:10:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they are conquerors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.61,0:10:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As you watch and listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.49,0:10:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,look for specific actions they took
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.66,0:10:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to maintain their peace
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.20,0:10:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and please give thoughtful attention
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.33,0:10:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to ways that you can imitate their faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.88,0:10:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up, I wondered,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.34,0:10:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why does the Supreme Judge, God,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.51,0:10:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,allow injustice and suffering?’
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And inside of me,\NI had this need to restore justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.52,0:11:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was such a burning desire within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.73,0:11:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I moved to Russia to stay with my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She started to study the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.45,0:11:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and was overflowing with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.29,0:11:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked for hours till late into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.96,0:11:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s when my special relationship\Nwith Jehovah began.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when I got a taste of what it’s like
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.13,0:11:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a caring Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It had been a while\Nsince I was able to feel that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.43,0:11:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My baptism date was very exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual family I inherited\Nwas very vast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.78,0:12:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You can instantly feel the love.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.66,0:12:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized,\Nand it seemed like miracles happened
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.08,0:12:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one after the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.00,0:12:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a great life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.18,0:12:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the persecution started\Nwith Brother Christensen,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there was a ripple effect\Nof arrests, one after the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.98,0:12:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it was our turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.90,0:12:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In June of 2018,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a huge group of armed men came to us,\Nto our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They represented the ideals of my childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But now these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.95,0:12:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,this judicial system,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.17,0:12:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,became the source of injustice to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:13:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting in a cage,\Nthe same way my bugs used to be in a jar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.26,0:13:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I felt like they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.77,0:13:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In your head\Nat that moment when you hear the verdict
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.98,0:13:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’ll stay in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s like you’ve been knocked unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.82,0:13:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve been hit in the head with something,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and there’s just a ringing sound\Nin your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.87,0:13:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I was taken away in handcuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.42,0:13:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I wasn’t in the best mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.38,0:13:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.88,0:13:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the doors of the elevator opened up,\Nand in front of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.65,0:14:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.69,0:14:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,were clapping their hands\Nas hard as they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.32,0:14:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And some were crying,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but not crying\Nbecause they felt sorry for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.91,0:14:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They cried because they loved us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.00,0:14:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and because they were proud of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.88,0:14:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what always happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.09,0:14:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re just about to lose\Nall your strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.97,0:14:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does that something for you\Nthat gives you a second wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.26,0:14:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, the applause, the love,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.35,0:14:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.77,0:14:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the shouts,\N“Hang in there; everything will be OK!”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.10,0:14:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—they gave me a second wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.78,0:14:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And with renewed strength,\NI could run the next part of the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.62,0:14:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the guards was so surprised\Nthat he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.91,0:14:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now that’s some support you’ve got!”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.87,0:14:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Without friends, I would be very lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.55,0:15:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I would constantly be focusing on my illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.42,0:15:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The day I met Marissa was at a convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s a really great friend,\Na spiritual friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When she’d take me\Nto my hospital appointments,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we would eat out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.06,0:15:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I think food is just the common language\Nbetween everyone, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.27,0:15:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When you talk about food, you know,\Nit’s like:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.73,0:15:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Ah! Yes, we have something to talk about,”\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be excited when she would take me\Nto my hospital appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She always makes me laugh, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.66,0:15:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She always helps me have a good time\Nno matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, friends really help encourage me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.79,0:15:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 17:17 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.38,0:15:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“A true friend shows love at all times
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.26,0:15:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and is a brother who is born\Nfor times of distress.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.68,0:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have seen this come true in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.97,0:15:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When I lost my job at the bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.97,0:15:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I felt very depressed, troubled, tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.85,0:16:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have a good friend who I can talk to,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.94,0:16:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I told him how I was feeling,\Nhe told me:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.73,0:16:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look, Miguel, don’t look for the same
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.24,0:16:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“line of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.24,0:16:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Maybe what you need to do\Nis make a change in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.79,0:16:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why don’t you find some simple work\Noutside of an office for a time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.67,0:16:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“That can help you to keep your eye simple
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.17,0:16:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow you to provide for your family.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.09,0:16:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched my wife make bread for our family,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.55,0:16:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and one day I told her:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.56,0:16:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’m going to make that bread,\Nbut not for our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.48,0:16:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to make it to sell.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.23,0:16:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So she told me, “No, are you crazy?”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.61,0:16:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a big change—right?—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.11,0:16:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,from having a position at a bank
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and handling a lot of money
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.20,0:16:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to selling on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I told her,\N“Look, I’m going to put this hat on,”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.29,0:16:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and I put like a chef’s hat on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.33,0:17:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.42,0:17:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’ll be back in less than an hour,\Nwhether I sell or not.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.21,0:17:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.84,0:17:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And to her surprise,\NI came back without any bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.51,0:17:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I got ready\Nto leave the second time to sell,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.68,0:17:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,she said: “OK. Go, but leave the hat here.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.20,0:17:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I also started to iron clothes\Nfor people in their homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.08,0:17:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it looked strange\Nbecause normally where we live
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.50,0:17:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that type of work is done by a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But for a man to go and iron clothes\Nat someone’s home,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.34,0:17:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you don’t see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.09,0:17:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn’t want to just sit back\Nwith my arms crossed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.09,0:17:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to put my hands to work\Nto earn a living for my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would preach one day,\Nand the next day I would iron clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.69,0:18:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day I would preach, and the day\Nafter that I would go out and sell bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.15,0:18:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So my mind was always occupied\Non doing something,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.69,0:18:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,either for the Kingdom or my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.86,0:18:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that helped me a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.37,0:18:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was feeling so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.37,0:18:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I really needed Jehovah’s help\Nto figure out what was going on with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.08,0:18:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.25,0:18:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that the 2009 article about depression\Ncame out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.05,0:18:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized: ‘OK, Jehovah,\Nyou’re telling me this is what I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.60,0:18:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘So now that I realize I have this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.68,0:18:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to figure out how I can manage it.’
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.10,0:18:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I changed my eating habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.52,0:18:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I started exercising a lot more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.56,0:18:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that exercising and eating healthy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,really, really did help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, I made a journal,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and I made different sections
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.54,0:19:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the different aspects of my depression\Nthat I dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In each section, I would put scriptures;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.29,0:19:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I would put articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.38,0:19:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the illustrations, the pictures,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.38,0:19:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they speak a lot without saying anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah hears us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.85,0:19:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.15,0:19:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,After some time in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they transferred me to a different cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.07,0:19:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In it were inmates who followed the orders
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.74,0:19:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.78,0:19:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They did everything they could\Nto other inmates
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.91,0:19:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to make life unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.63,0:19:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did they do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.63,0:19:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To break a person
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.80,0:19:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they would start to collaborate\Nwith the investigators,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:20:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,confess to everything, and then be able\Nto get transferred to another area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.02,0:20:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 37:3:\N“Trust in Jehovah and do what is good.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.94,0:20:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I said: “Jehovah, please help me\Nto stay loyal to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.24,0:20:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.65,0:20:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My prayers were really simple
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.70,0:20:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,—actually like two words: “Jehovah, help!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.95,0:20:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, help! Jehovah, help!”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.45,0:20:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite how they treated me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.58,0:20:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I dealt with others,\NI tried to treat them with kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.84,0:20:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These people,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they made life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.34,0:20:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomfortable, unbearable,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.72,0:20:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but when they were treated kindly,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.30,0:20:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they started to soften.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They began to treat me differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.94,0:20:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was being transferred
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.98,0:20:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that cell,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.02,0:20:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the inmate who ran the area\Ncalled me over to him and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.03,0:21:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come sit beside me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.99,0:21:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I sat down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.24,0:21:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he said, “If anybody in this prison\Ntouches you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.87,0:21:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,tell him that I’ll come looking for him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.96,0:21:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he said, “Get his things”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.13,0:21:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,(he told the other prisoners).
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.55,0:21:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The cell doors opened
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and the guards saw
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.30,0:21:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a crowd of inmates
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.72,0:21:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,grabbing my things\Nand putting them out into the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.69,0:21:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I left the cell\Nwithout having to carry a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The guard quietly closed the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.57,0:21:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And before the inmates\Nreturned to their cells,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.95,0:21:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,they even said goodbye, hugged me,\Nand said: “Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.12,0:21:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re going to be OK.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.33,0:21:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They went into the cell, and the guard\Nclosed the door and asked me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.54,0:21:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Boy, how long have you been in there?”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.62,0:21:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Three weeks.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:22:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “Well, normally\Npeople leave this cell beaten up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.55,0:22:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they’re thrown out by the other inmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.88,0:22:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“They have to carry their own things,\Nand that’s if the other inmates
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.60,0:22:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,haven’t thrown their stuff out the door.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.68,0:22:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn’t believe what had just happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.18,0:22:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.77,0:22:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Exercising, changing my diet,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.57,0:22:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the publications, journaling\N—that was my lifeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.49,0:22:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That really actually helped me\Nfor a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.37,0:22:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But it came to a point\Nwhere it stopped working as effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.62,0:22:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember getting ready,\Ndressing for the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.87,0:22:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.00,0:22:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was getting dressed for the meeting\Nand about to walk out the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.05,0:22:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but I couldn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.38,0:22:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There was this overwhelming fear\Nthat came over me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.59,0:22:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and an overwhelming sadness\Nthat came over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.80,0:22:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just lost it; I just started crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.56,0:22:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t get myself together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.14,0:22:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It was bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.19,0:22:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It got really bad;\Nmy depression got really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.99,0:23:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was very difficult for me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to approach the brothers\Nto ask them for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.53,0:23:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But at that time, I knew that if I didn’t,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.45,0:23:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,something bad would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.71,0:23:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I decided: ‘You know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.42,0:23:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to ask for a shepherding call\Nwith my brothers,’
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.26,0:23:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because I’d never talked about my depression\Nwith the elders at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.59,0:23:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This was my first time speaking with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.05,0:23:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was one brother, one of the elders,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.27,0:23:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who also battled depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.64,0:23:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And he suggested,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.73,0:23:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Have you thought\Nabout seeking medical help?”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.82,0:23:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeking professional help\Nwas something I never wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.28,0:23:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that I didn’t need to do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.74,0:23:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but sometimes there comes a point where
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.45,0:23:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you need additional help
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.79,0:24:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you’re doing is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.30,0:24:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In this world, they make you feel\Nthat it’s a bad thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.17,0:24:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that depression is a dirty word,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.18,0:24:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or that seeking medical help\Nis something that you don’t do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.80,0:24:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But I realized also
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.97,0:24:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that seeking medical help
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.27,0:24:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was part of my being able\Nto worship Jehovah effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.02,0:24:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s me doing my part.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.73,0:24:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everyone needs to take that step,\Nbut for me, this is what I need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.28,0:24:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m glad I did it because of the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.90,0:24:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’ve never ever felt this good
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.29,0:24:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.16,0:24:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,About a year later,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.96,0:24:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we were released.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.09,0:24:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But my wife and I understood
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.42,0:24:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that they could put me back in prison again,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.55,0:24:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.60,0:24:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we needed to use\Nthe time until then to the full
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.85,0:24:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the best way possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.69,0:25:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.48,0:25:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 119:165:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.23,0:25:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Abundant peace belongs to those\Nwho love your law.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.41,0:25:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We had family worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.33,0:25:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,read the Bible, and prayed together.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.66,0:25:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how I spent my four months of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.55,0:25:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I was put into prison
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.80,0:25:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.93,0:25:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When they told me\Nabout my cancer being gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.14,0:25:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really happy; I was ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.65,0:25:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like: ‘Finally I’m going\Nto get to do normal things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.73,0:25:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that a kid my age should be able to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.57,0:25:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t need to be afraid\Nor anxious anymore.’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.12,0:26:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I did relapse again,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.37,0:26:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and basically right now\Nmy present condition is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.88,0:26:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s nothing really more to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.88,0:26:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re just waiting\Nto let nature take its course basically,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.30,0:26:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.39,0:26:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In harmony with Ephesians 4:26,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.98,0:26:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to let myself process the news
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.69,0:26:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and let myself be sad and be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.07,0:26:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let yourself feel those feelings;
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.20,0:26:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,do not try to repress them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.20,0:26:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can control\Nyour thoughts and your actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.45,0:26:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty much my whole life\Nhas revolved around my illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.71,0:26:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’ve learned how to shift focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.09,0:26:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don’t focus on myself all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.67,0:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I focus on others and their trials,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.30,0:26:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which are different but just as hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.51,0:27:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You read the stories\Non jw.org in the Newsroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.93,0:27:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Russian brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.44,0:27:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray for them constantly because
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.61,0:27:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they are going through a very tough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.15,0:27:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is [definitely] more happiness\Nin giving than receiving.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.49,0:27:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And in our situation, this proved true.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.62,0:27:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.16,0:27:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this really helps to relieve your pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.71,0:27:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you focus on yourself,\Nyour pain gets worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.75,0:27:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When you focus on others\Nand on their problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.09,0:27:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,your pain lessens, diminishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.82,0:27:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.95,0:27:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.32,0:28:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Antoinette, I was so—
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.45,0:28:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was told\Nthat we would talk with each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.75,0:28:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this was something very special for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.63,0:28:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Same for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.38,0:28:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When the brothers told me as well
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.88,0:28:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,about meeting you, I was really excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.38,0:28:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your prayers\Nin behalf of the brothers in Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.10,0:28:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They are precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.06,0:28:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We can learn so much from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.23,0:28:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.36,0:28:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s really nice of you to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.07,0:28:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve both been through very many hardships.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.36,0:28:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure prison was super hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.99,0:28:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, in prison,\Nus brothers had a saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.42,0:28:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you ask: ‘How much worse can it get?’
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.55,0:28:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you won’t have to wait long to find out.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.30,0:29:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Or in other words, when you think,\N‘How much worse can it get?’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.30,0:29:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for sure something worse is bound to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.72,0:29:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we received our sentence,\Nwe thought:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.44,0:29:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, that’s it.\NThat’s the worst that could happen.’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.49,0:29:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course, it got worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.45,0:29:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon arrival at the prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.87,0:29:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we were beaten up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.71,0:29:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and for hours we were humiliated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought, ‘How much worse can it get?’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.56,0:29:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the next day, we were told,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.98,0:29:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are going to the punishment cell.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.06,0:29:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.07,0:30:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, how much worse can it get?’
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.69,0:30:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, it started with one floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.41,0:30:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,then it went to another floor,\Nand then the whole entire hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.33,0:30:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Every floor had COVID patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.92,0:30:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That was some of the hardest nursing\Nthat I’ve ever done in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.92,0:30:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of my years of nursing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.59,0:30:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we lost a lot of good nurses
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.76,0:30:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,who were right in the trenches with me\Nwho were in there doing their best.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.35,0:30:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We lost a lot of good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.35,0:30:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I was on medication to help me,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.31,0:30:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it still didn’t take the depression away.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.52,0:30:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re like: ‘What’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.82,0:30:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I can’t save anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.61,0:30:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t, I can’t help anyone.’
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.82,0:30:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was devastating.\NIt truly, truly was devastating.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.71,0:30:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt as Feliks did\Nwhen he asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.59,0:31:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“How much worse can it get?”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.38,0:31:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, a spiritual person
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.84,0:31:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,can see each new challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.22,0:31:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as an opportunity to rely on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.02,0:31:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As we watch\Nthe concluding part of this video,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.23,0:31:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,please take note of how Jehovah strengthened
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.69,0:31:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,these brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.69,0:31:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and deepened their friendship with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.57,0:31:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about your own circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.53,0:31:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ways that Jehovah\Nhas helped you through trials,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.12,0:31:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and have full confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.12,0:31:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will continue to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.88,0:31:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I decided\Nthat I was going to stop asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.89,0:31:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“How much worse could it get?”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.60,0:31:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked Jehovah for endurance
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.97,0:31:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and joy for that day—just for that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.86,0:32:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And at those times, I just
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.32,0:32:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,cry to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.11,0:32:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,talk to Jehovah about how I’m feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.70,0:32:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and just ask for his peace\Nto help me to deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.12,0:32:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve talked to Jehovah\Nvery intimately and personally
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.63,0:32:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but never like I have\Nwhen I was so alone there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.26,0:32:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I was going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.93,0:32:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked Jehovah if he saw enough good in me,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.19,0:32:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would just resurrect me
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.23,0:32:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I’d love to be in his new world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.98,0:32:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and see my husband again and my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.32,0:32:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thanked him so much\Nfor the life that I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.04,0:32:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I felt such a peace
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.21,0:33:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,like I’d never felt before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.09,0:33:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.59,0:33:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I just knew it was Jehovah getting me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.97,0:33:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The obedience, just doing what we were told,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.68,0:33:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it came from Jehovah, and it was so simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.56,0:33:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That gave him something to bless,\Nand it may have saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.86,0:33:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I just never wanted to be a burden on people,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.12,0:33:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.74,0:33:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers and sisters\Nhad come from all over the country
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.29,0:33:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to do work for this house\Nand the other houses—all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.59,0:33:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They made me feel wanted,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.38,0:33:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and they made me feel loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.43,0:33:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To feel like Jehovah cared enough\Nto give attention to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.89,0:34:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.52,0:34:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,just felt so unworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.60,0:34:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And here all these people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.31,0:34:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are here taking care of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.32,0:34:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just look at them,\Nand then you think:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.82,0:34:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m part of this organization.\NI’ve got to do better.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.03,0:34:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to be like them\Nand make other people happy.’
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.13,0:34:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When I’m able to help people\Nwho are battling depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.13,0:34:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like Jehovah is using me in that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.71,0:34:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it makes me happy\Nthat I can be of use to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.64,0:34:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good to feel—\NIt’s so nice to feel good again,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.89,0:34:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel happy again, to be able to smile,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.18,0:34:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to take in enjoyment
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.19,0:34:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the small things, you know,\Nin Jehovah’s creation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.23,0:34:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—and, you know, just be happy that I’m alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.15,0:34:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.74,0:34:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.46,0:35:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have a stable job.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.75,0:35:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I work at a hardware store.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.21,0:35:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel at peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.59,0:35:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The adversities have made me stronger,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.26,0:35:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and overall, I have\Na much closer relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.22,0:35:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m still making bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.60,0:35:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And at home, yeah,\NI’m the one who irons the clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.56,0:35:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, I found out\Nthat I was being deported.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.57,0:35:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember getting off the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.87,0:35:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They took me through the back door,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.87,0:35:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but my wife, Zhenya,\Nwas standing at the main entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.41,0:35:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She was on the phone. She couldn’t see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.08,0:35:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She was looking at the main entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.58,0:35:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I threw my bag down as I ran to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.59,0:35:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She could see from the corner of her eyes\Nsomeone was running.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.85,0:36:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She was a little confused, even scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.52,0:36:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And there I was
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.57,0:36:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,hugging the person I loved the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.78,0:36:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was one\Nof the most beautiful days of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.13,0:36:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.34,0:36:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Privet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.17,0:36:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.43,0:36:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard that you were praying for us
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.43,0:36:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the brothers and sisters in Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.85,0:36:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it really encouraged me and Feliks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.86,0:36:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s such an example for me personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.94,0:36:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned it in our prayer yesterday;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.94,0:36:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Feliks was saying
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.95,0:37:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are a great example\Nof how we need
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.03,0:37:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to genuinely care\Nfor our brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.41,0:37:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We love you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.80,0:37:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.76,0:37:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.72,0:37:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was nice meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.77,0:37:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.10,0:37:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My cancer is uncurable,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.11,0:37:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but I know the cure is in the new system.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.36,0:37:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s the cure!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.57,0:37:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I like to imagine, ‘When that time happens,\Nwhat will I be doing?’
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.33,0:37:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, I’m going to be jumping for joy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.54,0:37:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because I’m going to be rid of my cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.42,0:37:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to enjoy food\Nthat we never really got to enjoy,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.71,0:38:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m going to have so many animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.13,0:38:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to make a house.\NI’m going to learn how to make a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.06,0:38:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace in this world is not the absence
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.72,0:38:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.44,0:38:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,danger,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.65,0:38:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,persecution,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.90,0:38:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or economic problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.28,0:38:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace in this world\Nis listening to Jehovah’s guidance,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.70,0:38:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,praying to Jehovah constantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.21,0:38:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,meditating on Jehovah’s Word\Nand his promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.80,0:38:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace in this world is also
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.55,0:38:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,having good friends by our side
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.97,0:38:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and having a good sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.60,0:38:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What I’ve learned from all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.61,0:39:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is peace isn’t from what’s outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.15,0:39:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,from what’s going on,\Nor from what you’re experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.61,0:39:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve learned that peace is on the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.62,0:39:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and that comes from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.38,0:39:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,These examples we’ve just seen
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.75,0:39:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are of ordinary people
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.96,0:39:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“with feelings like ours.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.38,0:39:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, they felt peace
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.18,0:39:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,even when confronting serious trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.06,0:39:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How did they do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.52,0:39:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When Miguel lost his job,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.06,0:39:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he kept his focus on serving Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.69,0:39:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was not too proud to do humble work
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.36,0:39:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide for his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.36,0:39:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Margaret was prepared for a natural disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.79,0:39:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and throughout her ordeal,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.29,0:39:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,she prayed to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.62,0:40:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,While struggling with depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.21,0:40:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nikki did research using our publications
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.38,0:40:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked for help from the elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.43,0:40:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when facing brutal persecution,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.26,0:40:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Feliks showed kindness to his persecutors.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.27,0:40:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew that the way he responded
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.48,0:40:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,would reflect Christian qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.94,0:40:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And dear Antoinette,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.99,0:40:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,despite her diagnosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.78,0:40:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,focuses not on herself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.95,0:40:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but on helping others.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.83,0:40:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As she said, the cure for her
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.12,0:40:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—as it is for all of us—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.25,0:40:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is God’s Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.04,0:40:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are experiencing trials,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.76,0:40:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on what you can control,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.72,0:40:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,help others,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.72,0:40:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,be grateful,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.72,0:40:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and rely on Jehovah and his organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.27,0:41:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are not experiencing serious trials,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.07,0:41:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,do what you can to prepare for them
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.03,0:41:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by building yourself up spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.41,0:41:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.62,0:41:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear of what might happen
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.37,0:41:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is often worse than the trial itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.83,0:41:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in Jehovah, and be assured
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.13,0:41:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will never abandon his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.59,0:41:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The dear brothers and sisters\Nwhom we’ve just listened to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.14,0:41:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,are doing well spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.89,0:41:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank them\Nfor participating in these interviews.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.40,0:41:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d also like to thank\Nall our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.11,0:41:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,working in the medical field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.44,0:41:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who have gone the extra mile\Nduring this pandemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.91,0:41:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,James 5:11 reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.87,0:42:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“We consider happy those who have endured.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.37,0:42:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“You have heard of the endurance of Job
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.25,0:42:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“and have seen the outcome Jehovah gave,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.75,0:42:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is very tender in affection\Nand merciful.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.68,0:42:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The blessings we receive by enduring trials
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.10,0:42:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can strengthen us for the future
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.97,0:42:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and help us to become the kind of person
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.35,0:42:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah wants us to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.65,0:42:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner peace and joy we experience
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.03,0:42:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is a gift from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.41,0:42:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As these brothers and sisters\Nfrom around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.91,0:42:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have reminded us,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.99,0:42:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we need never doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.33,0:42:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that our wonderful heavenly Father will bless
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.00,0:42:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all those who continue loving him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.22,0:42:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank all of the sisters and brothers\Nwho were interviewed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.22,0:43:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for their sincere comments
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.22,0:43:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and for allowing us to benefit and learn\Nfrom their experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.10,0:43:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Those candid interviews show
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.19,0:43:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can remain at peace
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.48,0:43:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,even when enduring severe trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.16,0:43:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah always supports and cares for us,\Nhis loyal servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.91,0:43:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The time has now come\Nfor the baptism discourse.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.67,0:43:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We encourage all baptism candidates\Nto pay particular attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.13,0:43:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How does walking in Jehovah’s way\Nbring peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.13,0:43:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we stay on the road\Nto everlasting life?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.10,0:43:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please listen carefully\Nas Brother William Turner,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.89,0:43:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Service Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.89,0:43:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,delivers the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.06,0:43:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go On Walking ‘in the Way of Peace.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.28,0:43:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot express
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.91,0:44:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to you baptism candidates around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.91,0:44:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,how much of a privilege it is for us
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.41,0:44:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to share in this occasion with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.33,0:44:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You are following through\Non the most important decision
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.92,0:44:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ve ever made
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.92,0:44:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—to make it known publicly
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.13,0:44:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have dedicated your life to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.22,0:44:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We know your situations vary.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.89,0:44:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you candidates\Nwere raised knowing about Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.43,0:44:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but you had to develop your own\Npersonal relationship with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.81,0:44:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Others of you may be taking this step
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.32,0:44:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,after learning about Jehovah more recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.44,0:44:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever your circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.07,0:44:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,likely it was a journey
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.28,0:44:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—a figurative road\Nyou had to travel to get to this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.04,0:44:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the Bible also compares true worship
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.87,0:44:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to a road, a path,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.96,0:44:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or a walkway that has to be traveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.63,0:44:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At Acts 9:2,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.84,0:45:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as the first-century\NChristian congregation was being established,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.47,0:45:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ disciples used the term “The Way”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.31,0:45:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to designate their newly established\Nform of worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.81,0:45:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They understood that as baptized Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.94,0:45:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they were walking on a new path
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.44,0:45:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and every aspect of their lives was involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.41,0:45:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s going to be\Nthe case for you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.08,0:45:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, note how the Bible describes this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.45,0:45:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn with me, please,\Nto the book of Ephesians.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.50,0:45:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And note what is stated\Nin Ephesians chapter 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.50,0:45:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll read verses 22 through 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.35,0:45:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There it says: “You were taught\Nto put away the old personality
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.81,0:45:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“that conforms\Nto your formal course of conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.69,0:46:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“and that is being corrupted\Naccording to its deceptive desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.74,0:46:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“And you should continue to be made new
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.53,0:46:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“in your dominant mental attitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.45,0:46:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“and should put on the new personality
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.79,0:46:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“that was created according to God’s will
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.37,0:46:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in true righteousness and loyalty.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.50,0:46:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So like the first-century Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.25,0:46:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you have come to know\Nthe truth about Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.13,0:46:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the things you’ve learned
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.51,0:46:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,have led you to become baptism candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.93,0:46:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Like all of God’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.06,0:46:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ve done what verse 22 states,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.14,0:46:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“put away the old personality.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.31,0:46:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But there in verse 23,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.27,0:46:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we must also “continue to be made new
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.78,0:46:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in [our] dominant mental attitude.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.20,0:46:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This involves our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.33,0:46:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—what we allow our mind to dwell on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.16,0:46:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you know, the footnote for that verse
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.58,0:46:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,indicates this term could also be rendered
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.09,0:47:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as “the force actuating [our] mind”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.09,0:47:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or literally translated\N“to the spirit of your mind.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.05,0:47:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In the English language,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.06,0:47:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps you’ve heard someone say\Nthat they are in good spirits
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.43,0:47:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or you’ve heard someone\Ndescribed as being mean-spirited.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.19,0:47:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s a description\Nof one’s dominant mental attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.15,0:47:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—one’s thoughts and motivations.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.41,0:47:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s what moves us to act the way that we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.71,0:47:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal as baptized servants of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.87,0:47:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is to gain a dominant mental attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.67,0:47:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that aligns and is in harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.26,0:47:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with God’s thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.05,0:47:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that won’t always be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.93,0:47:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes time and a lot of effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.68,0:47:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who walk\Nin the way of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.85,0:47:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,often encounter trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.94,0:48:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And to stay on that road,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.61,0:48:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we must be willing to make sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.57,0:48:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Like some of those first-century Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.49,0:48:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we may have to endure direct persecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.58,0:48:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we continue to walk in Jehovah’s way,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.25,0:48:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.63,0:48:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah is going to bless us.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.96,0:48:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,At Luke 1:79, he assures us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.55,0:48:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will “guide our feet\Nin the way of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.01,0:48:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a comforting thought, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.64,0:48:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.31,0:48:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re excited that you baptism candidates
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.65,0:48:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,have undertaken this journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.90,0:48:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And know that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.90,0:48:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,some eight and a half million\Nother Witnesses on this road with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.65,0:48:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And today,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.66,0:48:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it is our honor and privilege to welcome you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.20,0:48:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—to welcome you to Jehovah’s way of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.12,0:49:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and “the road leading off into life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.42,0:49:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As we go through our discussion today,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.42,0:49:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to answer three questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.09,0:49:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,First, why is it important\Nthat we do not give up
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.72,0:49:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on walking in Jehovah’s way of peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.97,0:49:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Second,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.98,0:49:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,how does walking\Nin Jehovah’s way bring us peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.27,0:49:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And third, what can we do
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.57,0:49:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue walking\Nin Jehovah’s way of peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.07,0:49:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s address our first question:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.28,0:49:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it important that we do not give up
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.04,0:49:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,on walking in Jehovah’s way of peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.29,0:49:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to answer that, let’s turn, please,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.33,0:49:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to 2 Corinthians chapter 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.96,0:49:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll note
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.38,0:49:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Corinthians 4:16-18.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.64,0:49:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There it reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.56,0:50:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, we do not give up,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.56,0:50:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“but even if the man\Nwe are outside is wasting away,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.27,0:50:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“certainly the man we are inside\Nis being renewed from day to day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.07,0:50:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“For though the tribulation\Nis momentary and light,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.41,0:50:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“it works out for us a glory
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.91,0:50:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“that is of more and more\Nsurpassing greatness and is everlasting;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.41,0:50:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“while we keep our eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.42,0:50:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“not on the things seen,\Nbut on the things unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.04,0:50:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the things seen are temporary,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.92,0:50:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but the things unseen are everlasting.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.60,0:50:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see why we can’t give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.60,0:50:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because being one of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.10,0:50:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,requires that we remain active
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.56,0:50:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and persevere in the way of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.65,0:50:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You dear candidates have not given up\Nin your efforts to please Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.82,0:50:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and to qualify to become part of his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.41,0:50:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.12,0:51:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because of your love for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.54,0:51:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know that any trials\Nand obstacles you face now
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.29,0:51:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are “momentary and light”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.04,0:51:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when compared to an eternity\Nin God’s new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.05,0:51:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, you will enter\Ninto a special relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.34,0:51:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.35,0:51:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So don’t let anyone or anything
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.14,0:51:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,jeopardize that relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.77,0:51:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let it be something that you cherish
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.44,0:51:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because that relationship is everlasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.40,0:51:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So keep walking in Jehovah’s way of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.32,0:51:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on what it means\Nto have him as a Friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.66,0:51:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to have him guiding your steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.16,0:51:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t give up,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.42,0:51:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then despite any trials you face,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.42,0:51:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you will continue\Nto enjoy Jehovah’s blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.17,0:51:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re confident that you can do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.89,0:52:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But to highlight how this can be done,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.06,0:52:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.06,0:52:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re pleased to introduce\NSister Indira Alfonso.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.64,0:52:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Alfonso was baptized in 2006
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.90,0:52:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and now serves with her husband\Nas Bethel family members in Warwick.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.19,0:52:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Alfonso,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.20,0:52:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,can you tell us a little about your journey,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.99,0:52:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how you became associated\Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.66,0:52:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was born in Cuba,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.37,0:52:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but my mom and I moved\Nto the United States when I was nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.08,0:52:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I was young,\NI felt it was important to look for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.46,0:52:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So whenever we moved,\NI would visit the local churches in the area,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.30,0:52:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,even getting baptized in a number of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.59,0:52:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 11, my mom\Nlet me move in with my aunt,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.39,0:52:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,who was one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.39,0:52:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there, she asked my mom\Nif I could study with a pioneer sister
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.14,0:52:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from her congregation, and my mom agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.52,0:52:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s nice to see\Nthat even at a young age
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.48,0:52:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you had a spiritual need.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.69,0:52:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So during this time\Nleading up to your baptism
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.03,0:53:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.07,0:53:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,did you encounter any trials\Nthat threatened to make you give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.58,0:53:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did.\NI made changes very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.83,0:53:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped celebrating holidays\Nand stopped praying to idols.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.83,0:53:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But these changes\Nwere very strange to my mom
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.34,0:53:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—just difficult for her to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.01,0:53:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She was really afraid\Nthat I was being brainwashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.88,0:53:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So after studying for several months,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.14,0:53:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,she had me move back in with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.47,0:53:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which meant the end of my studies\Nand no more attending meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.27,0:53:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t long before my association
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.02,0:53:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was affecting my speech and my behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.61,0:53:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I found myself easily influenced\Nto even celebrate my birthday again.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.90,0:53:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I could feel I was moving further away\Nfrom Jehovah instead of closer to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.45,0:53:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry to hear that, Sister Alfonso.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.16,0:53:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what helped you not to give up
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.99,0:53:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and to go on walking in the way of peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.25,0:53:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped me was the scripture\Nat Matthew 10:37,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.46,0:53:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where Jesus said:\N“Whoever has greater affection for father
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.17,0:53:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or mother than for me is not worthy of me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.13,0:54:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that a peaceful\Nrelationship with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.84,0:54:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,might mean no peace with my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.93,0:54:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But I knew that if I were\Nto ever gain my mom,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.43,0:54:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to walk with Jehovah\Nthe right way and not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.14,0:54:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So one night, I prayed to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.14,0:54:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,crying for forgiveness\Nand asking for his help.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.98,0:54:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And to my surprise,\Na few days later without any explanation,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.82,0:54:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,my mom had me move back in with my aunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.36,0:54:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I resumed my Bible studies,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.74,0:54:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and a year later\Nat the age of 15, I got baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.83,0:54:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah clearly heard\Nand answered your prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.41,0:54:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, have you seen\Ncontinued evidence of Jehovah’s guidance?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.71,0:54:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A good friend helped me to adjust the way\NI was communicating with my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.26,0:54:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So one day, I called her and expressed to her\Nhow much I truly appreciate and love her.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.14,0:54:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want us to be distant anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.01,0:54:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I explained to her\Nthat my love for her had never changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.77,0:54:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but my love for Jehovah had come first.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.94,0:54:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So that conversation\Nwas a turning point for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.94,0:55:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have had many positive discussions,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.57,0:55:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and she’s much more understanding\Nof my decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.32,0:55:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing Jehovah’s guidance in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.53,0:55:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,makes me determined\Nto continue walking in his way of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.70,0:55:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, Sister Alfonso.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.70,0:55:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate\Nyour faithful example and comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.75,0:55:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s address our second point.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.88,0:55:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How does walking in Jehovah’s way\Nbring us peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.76,0:55:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And to answer this,\Nwe’re going to compare the path,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.43,0:55:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or journey, you’ve taken on the road to life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.56,0:55:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with a literal road, or walkway.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.77,0:55:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And in making this comparison,\Nwe find a number of similarities.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.65,0:55:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,First, both roads have boundaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.24,0:55:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a purpose, and a destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.12,0:55:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s start\Nwith that first one: boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.58,0:55:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,On a literal road, we may see “Yield”
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.12,0:55:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or “Do Not Enter” signs,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.46,0:56:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,guardrails on the side of the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.00,0:56:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or lines on the road\Nto help us stay in our lane.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.97,0:56:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those are boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.26,0:56:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And those boundaries\Nare there for our protection
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.97,0:56:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because if we step outside of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.73,0:56:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we risk getting hurt or lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.94,0:56:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be great if we could tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.52,0:56:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that as you continue\Non the road to life after your baptism,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.61,0:56:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we would love to say that the rest\Nof your journey is smooth sailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.82,0:56:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll have nothing but safe travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.87,0:56:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But the reality is
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.75,0:56:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will face challenges\Nand tests of your faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.75,0:56:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The Devil will make sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.63,0:56:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He will make sure\Nthat you are confronted
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.51,0:56:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.76,0:56:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to do whatever he can
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.85,0:56:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to damage\Nyour special relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.69,0:57:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But we’re confident that you can succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.02,0:57:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be successful and avoid danger
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.36,0:57:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if you remain within the boundaries
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.61,0:57:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s way of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.86,0:57:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do you stay\Nwithin those boundaries?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.03,0:57:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,By continuing to learn\Nabout Jehovah’s laws
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.29,0:57:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and principles and obeying them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.46,0:57:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That obedience will not only protect you,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.05,0:57:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but it will give you inner peace
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.05,0:57:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,—peace that comes\Nfrom having a clean conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.60,0:57:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The next similarity between a literal road
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.56,0:57:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and being on the road to life\Nthat we’ll discuss
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.60,0:57:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is having a purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.77,0:57:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we travel on a literal road,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.65,0:57:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our plan usually is not to get on the road
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.24,0:57:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and just stand still (to become stationary)
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.41,0:57:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or watch other people or vehicles go by.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.08,0:57:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we’re there for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.75,0:58:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the road\Nis to enable movement
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.38,0:58:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—to help us get from one place to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.42,0:58:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in a similar sense,\Nbeing on Jehovah’s way of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.22,0:58:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to move forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.22,0:58:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to make continual spiritual progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.22,0:58:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, there are many ways\Nthat we can make spiritual advancement.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.10,0:58:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One important way\Nthat all Christians can do so
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.40,0:58:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is by cultivating spiritual qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.20,0:58:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so pleasing to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.99,0:58:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider with me, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.99,0:58:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 6:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.71,0:58:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what’s mentioned here\Nat Galatians chapter 6,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.50,0:58:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.55,0:58:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “So, then, as long as we\Nhave the opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.34,0:58:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“let us work what is good toward all,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.47,0:59:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but especially toward those\Nrelated to us in the faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.85,0:59:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way to advance spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.82,0:59:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is to look for ways\Nto do good things for others,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.99,0:59:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,both inside and outside the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.99,0:59:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This pandemic has afforded us\Nmany opportunities to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.58,0:59:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been able to call and check on others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.16,0:59:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and distribute food or supplies when needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.08,0:59:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And think of what our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.09,0:59:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,have done time and again to assist others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.38,0:59:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,during natural disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.30,0:59:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So take a minute and think\Nabout your local area.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.89,0:59:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you work what is good toward all?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.85,0:59:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there ones\Nthat need assistance getting food
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.98,0:59:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or running errands?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.23,0:59:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there someone who could use
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.69,0:59:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a good word of encouragement\Nto cheer them up?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.45,1:00:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we know individuals\Nwho have lost loved ones in death
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.08,1:00:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with whom we could share words of comfort
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.25,1:00:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe simply provide a listening ear?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.33,1:00:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, by displaying spiritual qualities
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.17,1:00:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—qualities such as kindness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.30,1:00:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion, hospitality, generosity—
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.80,1:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re going to feel deeply rewarded
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.51,1:00:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for doing these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.64,1:00:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re pleasing Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.89,1:00:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because you will show that your purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.48,1:00:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for being on the road to life
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.52,1:00:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is not just to save yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.19,1:00:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but to help others.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.11,1:00:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there was a third similarity\Nbetween being on a literal road
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.58,1:00:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and being on the road to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.75,1:00:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In both cases,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.75,1:00:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a destination
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.75,1:00:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that we want to reach.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.17,1:00:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Traveling on a literal path\Nwill eventually take you to your destination.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.17,1:00:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a Witness of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.18,1:01:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,our journey, our walk,\Non this figurative road
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.51,1:01:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,will lead us to our destination
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.85,1:01:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,—the goal of enjoying\Na peaceful friendship with God forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.61,1:01:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we long for that time\Nin God’s new world,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.86,1:01:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,even now we can experience\Nthe blessings and inner peace
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.87,1:01:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that come from a life of service to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.75,1:01:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have the privilege\Nto speak with Sister Gloria Herd.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.71,1:01:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Herd has been baptized\Nfor over 70 years
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.88,1:01:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and has enjoyed a rich spiritual life\Nin special full-time service
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.72,1:01:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with her husband,\NBrother Samuel Herd of the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.01,1:01:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Herd, you’ve had\Nmany rich spiritual blessings,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.39,1:01:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know that you’ve encountered\Nchallenges along the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.02,1:01:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you’ve carried out\Nthese assignments through the years,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.03,1:02:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,walking in Jehovah’s way of peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.74,1:02:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how have you managed\Nto enjoy greater inner peace?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.66,1:02:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve learned, Brother Turner,\Nthat if Jehovah gives you an assignment,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.50,1:02:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he will give you what you need to fulfill it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.58,1:02:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned and really benefited\Nfrom the traveling overseers and their wives.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.34,1:02:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It was such a privilege to serve along\Nwith these faithful brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.01,1:02:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and several of them had served me\Nand my family when I was very young.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.30,1:02:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So to see their faithfulness,\Nto see their happiness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.76,1:02:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see that they really had inner peace
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.39,1:02:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,really benefited me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.77,1:02:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned from that,\Nand I wanted to follow their example.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.02,1:02:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That help from others can be so valuable.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.53,1:02:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How else have you managed?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.53,1:02:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve enjoyed inner peace too\Nfrom praying to Jehovah a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.87,1:02:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Many times we had\Nvery little money or no money,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.95,1:02:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but we never missed a meal,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.96,1:02:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and we never missed any theocratic event.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.04,1:02:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned that having no money
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.38,1:03:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is not an obstacle to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.59,1:03:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He heard our prayers, he answered them,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.38,1:03:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was as if the blessing\Nsometimes just fell out of heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.51,1:03:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer can be so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.10,1:03:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for sharing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.10,1:03:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, how has walking\Nin Jehovah’s way of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.40,1:03:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,helped you to have peace with others?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.73,1:03:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked and lived with many sisters,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.11,1:03:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all had different personalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.86,1:03:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I learned that I had\Nto apply Romans 12:18,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.32,1:03:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where it says:\N“As far as it depends [upon me],
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.83,1:03:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,be peaceable with all men [and women].”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.91,1:03:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I learned that I have to adjust
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.75,1:03:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,my personality sometimes to keep peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.80,1:03:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This happened very often.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.55,1:03:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But one time, we moved in\Nwith a sister on Tuesday morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.47,1:03:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and something I said upset her very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.18,1:03:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She got very angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.19,1:03:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I decided not to pursue the issue
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.31,1:04:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because I had to live with her for a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.73,1:04:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just decided\Nto let her see by my conduct
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.86,1:04:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could never have meant\Nwhat she thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.82,1:04:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So as the week went by,\Nthe days went by, the tension lessened.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.12,1:04:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And by Monday when we left,\Nwe were the best of friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.96,1:04:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And she gave me a big hug,\Nand nothing more was said about the subject.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.13,1:04:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it sounds like you\Nhandled that beautifully, Sister Herd.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.34,1:04:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Your spiritual qualities were evident.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.34,1:04:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, finally, how has walking\Nin Jehovah’s way of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.18,1:04:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,helped you have peace with God?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.47,1:04:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when you see Jehovah act
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.60,1:04:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on your behalf over and over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.64,1:04:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes you feel that you have his approval.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.65,1:04:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that Sam and I are in our senior years,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.57,1:04:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we feel He has given us\N‘the desire of our heart’
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.07,1:04:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by allowing us to serve at Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.53,1:04:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which had been our goal for many years.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.16,1:04:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know that as long as\NI stay faithful to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.95,1:04:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he will continue to grant me inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.29,1:05:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have that confidence as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.83,1:05:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, Sister Herd.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.84,1:05:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We deeply appreciate your comments\Nand your encouraging expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.43,1:05:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s now address our final point.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.56,1:05:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to continue walking
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.14,1:05:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s way of peace?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.60,1:05:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s go back\Nto our illustration of the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.61,1:05:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,On a literal road,\Ntravelers may need to make adjustments
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.86,1:05:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in response to changing road conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.86,1:05:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or bad weather.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.91,1:05:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, as you go on walking\Nin the way of peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.41,1:05:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you will need to readjust your actions\Nand thinking from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.79,1:05:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, a circuit overseer\Nshared an interesting point
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.59,1:05:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding our thoughts\Nand attitudes on matters.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.09,1:05:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that they could either serve
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.09,1:05:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as a prison or a passport:
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.93,1:05:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a prison, in that our thoughts and actions
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.23,1:06:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,can confine or restrict us
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.06,1:06:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or a passport,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.61,1:06:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in that they can take us where we need to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.78,1:06:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, right now, we need to be
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.95,1:06:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and stay on this road to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.37,1:06:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to make sure\Nthat any needed adjustments are made
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.12,1:06:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in our thoughts and our actions
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.25,1:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we’re not confined or restricted
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.17,1:06:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in making spiritual progress.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.88,1:06:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what might be some areas
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.18,1:06:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’ll need to make adjustments?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.10,1:06:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, please, Paul’s words\Nin 2 Corinthians chapter 13.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.19,1:06:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll read 2 Corinthians 13:11.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.87,1:06:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says: “Finally, brothers,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.24,1:07:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“continue to rejoice, to be readjusted,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.33,1:07:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“to be comforted, to think in agreement,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.92,1:07:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“to live peaceably;
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.13,1:07:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the God of love\Nand of peace will be with you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.09,1:07:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice three areas in this verse
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.80,1:07:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,where Paul states we can make adjustments?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.97,1:07:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,First, he says: “Continue to rejoice.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.77,1:07:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We can lose our peace and joy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.81,1:07:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if we become overwhelmed\Nby the anxieties of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.74,1:07:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So in order to rejoice,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.91,1:07:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,can you make it a goal to focus on things
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.53,1:07:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that bring joy rather than sadness?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.08,1:07:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you’re not feeling well\Nor coping with chronic pain,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.04,1:07:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you can focus on God’s promise\Nof when no one will say:
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.25,1:07:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am sick.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.42,1:07:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re facing opposition for your beliefs,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.35,1:08:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on the fact\Nthat we’re part of a brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.18,1:08:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—a brotherhood that supports\Nand prays for us—
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.73,1:08:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and arrangements are in place\Nto keep us spiritually strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.40,1:08:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re discouraged by world events,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.82,1:08:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you can rejoice in the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.95,1:08:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have a hope for the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.03,1:08:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know how this all ends.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.70,1:08:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that better times are ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.83,1:08:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The point is, Don’t let negative thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.63,1:08:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,restrict or limit your progress.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.30,1:08:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, make the needed adjustments
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.47,1:08:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can move forward\Nand continue to rejoice.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.43,1:08:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Note another area for readjustment\Nthat Paul mentions in verse 11.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.60,1:08:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There he says: “Continue . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.77,1:08:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to think in agreement.”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.98,1:08:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There were members of the congregation
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.99,1:09:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the first century\Nthat were promoting apostate ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.95,1:09:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Others were introducing controversial ideas
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.04,1:09:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that were not directly unscriptural,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.96,1:09:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but they were divisive.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.29,1:09:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This resulted in bickering\Nand arguments over words,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.84,1:09:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,really creating\Na spiritually unhealthy atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.38,1:09:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what’s going to help us
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.39,1:09:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue to think in agreement?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.35,1:09:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Paul’s words at 2 Timothy 2:23
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.73,1:09:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to “reject foolish and ignorant debates,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.40,1:09:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that they produce fights.”
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.94,1:09:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we react strongly\Nwhen facing issues
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.16,1:09:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that clearly violate Jehovah’s moral laws.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.41,1:09:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But if no Scriptural principle\Nis being violated,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.29,1:09:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re wise to abstain\Nfrom promoting our personal opinions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.21,1:09:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to do all we can to avoid starting
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.92,1:10:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or being drawn into disagreements
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.18,1:10:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that can disrupt the peace\Nof the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.39,1:10:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, back in verse 11,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.72,1:10:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a third area where we can make adjustments
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.52,1:10:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is to continue “to live peaceably.”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.15,1:10:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice\Nfrom the interview with our sisters
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.69,1:10:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what they both did when challenged,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.82,1:10:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when faced with a challenge\Nthat threatened their peace?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.33,1:10:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They took the matter to Jehovah in prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.62,1:10:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They reflected on scriptures\Nfound in God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.33,1:10:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they looked to see\Nhow they could apply those verses
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.55,1:10:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in their particular situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.51,1:10:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It helped them to not only have inner peace
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.09,1:10:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but peace with others as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.89,1:10:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So let your spiritual qualities\Nshine through.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.44,1:10:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue to work on keeping peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.98,1:10:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,showing those qualities\Nof being loving and generous toward all,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.61,1:11:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but especially with our close family members,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.03,1:11:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they are Witnesses or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.83,1:11:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we want to conclude\Nby reminding you baptism candidates
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.70,1:11:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that today marks a significant milestone
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.67,1:11:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in your journey\Nin your relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.34,1:11:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So take the time to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.67,1:11:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what this day means for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.97,1:11:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so proud of all of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.10,1:11:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You will never regret\Nthe decision you have made
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.14,1:11:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to dedicate your life to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.77,1:11:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But keep in mind that after today and beyond,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.69,1:11:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the journey is not yet over.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.28,1:11:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, it’s just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.49,1:11:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we encourage you\Nto do all you can
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.16,1:11:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay on the road to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.87,1:11:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind the points we considered today.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.96,1:12:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,First, do not give up\Non walking in Jehovah’s way of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.96,1:12:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life depends on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.46,1:12:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow Jehovah to guide your steps.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.39,1:12:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, stay within the boundaries\Non the road to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.31,1:12:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, you’re walking with a purpose,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.35,1:12:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and that will lead you to your destination
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.06,1:12:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—peaceful friendship with Jehovah forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.74,1:12:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, keep making\Nany needed adjustments
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.95,1:12:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in your thoughts, attitude, and actions
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.24,1:12:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can maintain peace\Nwith Jehovah and peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.25,1:12:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you continue to do these things,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.92,1:12:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,not only will you have peace
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.63,1:12:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but as the last part\Nof 2 Corinthians 13:11 says:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.05,1:12:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“The God of love and of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.30,1:12:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will be with you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.64,1:12:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,May you always remember that promise,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.60,1:12:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which Jehovah makes to those
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.94,1:13:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who go on walking in the way of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.11,1:13:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Turner.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.49,1:13:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Similar to last year,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.49,1:13:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the arrangements for baptism\Nwill vary in each location.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.91,1:13:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Each local congregation’s elders\Nhave made suitable provisions
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.62,1:13:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in accord with local circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.00,1:13:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for candidates to be baptized\Nafter the conclusion of this session.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.00,1:13:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank Jehovah\Nfor the timely spiritual food we enjoyed
